The governments of the United States, United Kingdom, and French Republic have issued a joint statement on nuclear terrorism. They recognize the threat of nuclear terrorism and their collective responsibility to secure sensitive information, technology, and nuclear material from terrorists. They also aim to develop emergency response measures. The governments will engage in international workshops to enhance the effectiveness of physical protection measures for nuclear material. They also possess the knowledge and capability to handle and dispose of nuclear threat devices. They are committed to continuously improving their emergency detection and response assets and seek to strengthen worldwide preparedness against nuclear terrorism.